##Dictation. | I'm the suspect

Now those special infectious disease hospitals in Wuhan, bed tension, there are many people with a quilt covered in the hospital infusion, waiting for admission. Dictation | Yu Yi (alias)

To clean up the mess

My Name is Yu Yi, this year 34 years old, Hometown Huanggang, Hubei, is now a renovation workers in Wuhan. After the outbreak of the new pneumonia, I felt like a mild case. However, due to the overcrowding of my hospital visits and the lack of proper testing, I never became a confirmed case, even though I developed a number of classic symptoms.

Infection

I was very busy before the new year. I worked until January 20. I was busy until January 20, when I began to rest at home.

On the morning of January 22, I had to take a bus from Wuchang to Hanyang for work. It was a long trip, and I had to make three transfers. In fact, two days ago, I and the people around me also saw the news about the epidemic in the media, but I personally took a chance, always feel that the virus is far from their own.

A lot of people knew about it at the time, but when I went out that day, half the people on the road weren't wearing masks. A lot of people probably feel the same way as I do, but it's also possible that masks were really hard to find. On the 22nd, I went home. I was going back to my hometown in Huanggang as usual, but the next day (the 23rd) Wuhan closed the city and I never went out again. So later, I had symptoms of the disease, I think it should be the day out of the infected.

Check

On New Year's Eve, January 24th, I had dinner with my wife and two children at home, and I began to feel sick. The symptoms were fever, headache, and general malaise, with a fever of 37.8 degrees. On the 25th, I took anti-inflammatory drugs and became normal again. I thought it was just a common cold and fever. I didn't think about the new pneumonia. But by the 26th, I felt the symptoms getting worse and I had to go to the hospital.

So, early on the morning of the 27th, I went to the community hospital near home to take a film, showing "the left lower lobe multiple ground glass plate density increased shadow" , the diagnosis is "the left lower lobe multiple infection. At the time, I could sense that the people in the hospital were afraid of me, and told me to stay away from them while I got the report. I think I might have an infection, but I also understand them. Doctors and nurses are the hardest workers.

On the same day, the community hospital suggested that I immediately transfer to a large hospital, I was referred to the Tongji Hospital affiliated Tongji Hospital of Huazhong University of Science and Technology in Guanggu Hospital district, which is also relatively close to my large hospital.

That morning at Changzhou Community Hospital, there were three people with my symptoms, and then we all went to Tongji Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yu Yi's CT report form at the Community Hospital

I went to Tongji Hospital (Guanggu Hospital district) fever clinic, the most intuitive feeling is a lot of people, many are similar to their situation. The out-patient doctor read the report from the Community Hospital and told me that your symptoms were mild, that you should go home, take your medication, and then isolate yourself. I didn't get tested there, and I didn't get tested when I went back, so I was never diagnosed. But from my symptoms, to the preliminary examination results, and then to Tongji Hospital doctors to the Treatment Program, these let me think I was infected with new pneumonia, but the symptoms are relatively mild.

Symptoms, but I'm definitely not the only one who didn't get diagnosed. I was in Tongji Hospital (Guanggu Hospital district) , there are many older than me in the hospital and more seriously ill people, some even cough can not walk well. These people don't have beds either, so they just sit in the hallways and let the doctors give them shots. Personally, I think it has something to do with the fact that the nucleic acid test conditions didn't follow then, and I don't know if they follow now. In addition, I would like to say that since I have not been diagnosed, I have to pay for my own medicine. It costs about 300 yuan to buy a medicine, 600 yuan for two times, and nearly 1,000 yuan with other tests. Of course, I know that life must be the most important thing in this situation. No matter how much it costs, I still have to buy it.

Quarantined

After I returned home from Tongji Hospital on the 27th, I quarantined myself. In addition, according to the doctor's orders, I take medicine on time every day, a total of four. After a few days of this, I could feel myself slowly recovering and my symptoms were improving, and by the 30th I was almost normal. On the 30th, I went to Tongji Hospital (Guanggu Hospital district) for a review, but there were still many people, the doctor still did not give me a check. The doctor prescribed the same medicine and told me to go home and continue the quarantine until I was 14 days old.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Drugs Yu Yi is currently taking

I am now and my wife and children in Wuhan Three Ring Road South Longcheng rent housing, this side of the usual flow of people is larger. After the outbreak, the basic livelihood of our family is still guaranteed. There is a two-story supermarket chain nearby. The family used to go shopping there during the Spring Festival. When they came back, they said the vegetables and eggs were the best sellers. They sold very fast and the prices were a little higher than usual.

My current state of mind is relatively optimistic, as the symptoms gradually improve, life is gradually normal. That is, work has been affected. Originally, work started after the 15th day of the first lunar month. Now, it is not clear.

During this time away from home, I stayed in my room alone, relying on my cell phone to communicate with my family, or sometimes they could hear me yelling loudly in the room. Let the wife leave the meal at the door of the room. I have two children at home, one is ten years old and the other is seven. Da Wa probably understands my situation, still use mobile phone to smile to say to me: "Dad is quarantined. "

I'd love to go out and help them with their lives, but I can't. Later, I understand that to protect themselves, self-isolation, is the best protection for others. The good news is, the family's fine so far, no sign of infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yangsigang Yangtze River Bridge in Wuhan, photographed by Yu Yi

Finally, I look forward to an early end of the epidemic in Wuhan and other parts of the country, so that everyone's lives can return to normal as soon as possible.
